window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>Seven nights, one bed, and the last man I should want to share it with…I’m a hopeless romantic with a laughably tragic history with the opposite sex.</p> <p>Wesley’s a dirty talking lawyer with a wickedly talented tongue and a habit of showing up when I need rescuing from my latest bad date.</p> <p>But he’s also my best friend’s brother and off limits. That one red hot night we spent together was a mistake I’m determined not to make again…</p> <p>Until one cursed night, when I accidentally ignite a feud with the biggest troublemaker in town and wind up on Wes’s doorstep in a tattered bridesmaid’s dress, needing to get out of town—fast.</p> <p>Soon, Wes and I are on the run in a borrowed camper van, accompanied by my pet ferret and enough sexual tension to launch us all into outer space. Even worse?</p> <p>With every passing mile, he’s proving he truly might be my dream guy.</p> <p>But will he still want me when he realizes my cursed dating history isn’t the only tragic thing in my past?</p>"; 
